## What is this?

This is an **ADE (Agent Dev Environment)** — a Cursor workspace scaffolded from a [copier template](https://github.com/madi-parloa/ade-template). It contains:

- A portfolio of Parloa infrastructure repos cloned by copier `_tasks` from the answer-derived `ade-repos.txt`. Missing repos are cloned on both `copier copy` and `copier recopy`; already-cloned repos are never modified (safe for WIP).
- GSD (Get Shit Done) installed workspace-locally for spec-driven development. Refreshed on every `copier recopy` (tracks `@latest`).
- The `claudes-kitchen/` and `open-kitchen/` repos (when the `kitchens` group is selected) cloned as reference source. Their setup scripts are NOT auto-run — they mutate user/system state (see `claudes-kitchen/setup-cooking-environment.sh`). Run them manually if you want global installation.
- Pre-seeded codebase intelligence in `.planning/codebase/` so GSD is immediately Parloa-aware.
{%- if include_gsd_docs %}
- **gsd-docs** shared planning — `.planning/` is a symlink into `gsd-docs/`, backed by `parloa/gsd-docs` on the `docs` branch. Shared project context + personal implementation plans. See `gsd-docs/README.md`.
{%- endif %}

## Quick start

This ADE was created with:

```bash
uvx copier copy --trust git+https://github.com/madi-parloa/ade-template.git <this-directory>
```

## Updating

```bash
uvx copier recopy --trust --skip-answered --overwrite
```

Single entry point. Safe to run on a clean tree. `recopy` re-renders every template-owned file from the current template, so the latest template is what lands on disk:

- **`--trust`** — required (template uses `_tasks`: clone loop, GSD install, auto-commit).
- **`--overwrite`** — required on `recopy`; suppresses the per-file overwrite prompt ("template wins" is the whole point).
- **`--skip-answered`** — reuses stored answers for existing questions, but still prompts for any question newly introduced in a later template version — so template evolution surfaces once.

What `recopy` does:

- Re-renders every template file (`AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `README.md`, `.planning/codebase/*`, `.gitignore`, `ade-repos.txt`, `<ade>.code-workspace`, `agentic-stack.md`).
- Clones any repos newly listed in the rendered `ade-repos.txt`; existing repos are untouched (safe for WIP).
- Refreshes GSD via `npx -y get-shit-done-cc@latest --local --cursor`.
- Auto-commits everything as `chore: copier recopy to <hash>` (where `<hash>` is the template commit SHA) so the working tree is clean on return.

Consecutive recopies work with no manual `git commit` in between. If a conflict marker is somehow present (shouldn't happen under `--overwrite`), auto-commit is skipped and the tree is left for manual resolution.

## Changing the portfolio

`ade-repos.txt` and `<ade>.code-workspace` are generated from your copier answers — edits to those files are reverted on the next `recopy`. To change what repos this ADE includes:

```bash
uvx copier recopy --trust --overwrite
```

Omit `--skip-answered` and re-answer `portfolio_groups` and/or `extra_repos`. Your existing answers are the prompt defaults.

For a one-shot seeded input:

```bash
uvx copier recopy --trust --overwrite --data extra_repos="$(cat my-repos.txt)"
```

### Repo-name shorthand

`extra_repos` (and the group definitions in the template) use short names:

| You write | Resolved to | Folder |
|-----------|-------------|--------|
| `some-repo` | `git@github.com:parloa/some-repo.git` | `some-repo` |
| `madi-parloa/some-repo` | `git@github.com:madi-parloa/some-repo.git` | `some-repo` |
| `git@github.com:...` / `https://...` / `*.git` | pass-through | basename (stripping `.git`) |

Blank lines and `#` comments are ignored.

## Pulling existing clones (optional, manual)

`recopy` never `git pull`s repos you already have — doing so over your own WIP would be unsafe. When you do want to refresh all clones:

```bash
for d in */; do [ -d "$d/.git" ] && git -C "$d" pull --ff-only; done
```

